{"action": "edit", "code": "def find_non_zero_blocks(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[np.ndarray]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, this function finds the 9 3x3 blocks where there is no zero element in the block.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of 9 numpy arrays, where each array represents a 3x3 block with no zero element.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_zero_blocks = []\n    for i in range(0, 9, 3):\n        for j in range(0, 9, 3):\n            block = input_grid[i:i + 3, j:j + 3]\n            if not np.any(block == 0):\n                non_zero_blocks.append(block)\n    return non_zero_blocks\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.zeros((9, 9))\n    non_zero_blocks = find_non_zero_blocks(input_grid)\n    sorted_blocks = sort_blocks(non_zero_blocks)\n    output_grid = recombine_blocks(sorted_blocks)\n    return output_grid\ndef sort_blocks(non_zero_blocks: List[np.ndarray]) -> List[np.ndarray]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of non-zero blocks, this function sorts the blocks according to the average index of non-five element\n    and puts the all-five block in the middle of the non_zero_blocks.\n\n    Args:\n    non_zero_blocks: A list of numpy arrays representing the non-zero blocks.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of sorted numpy arrays, where each array represents a 3x3 block with no zero element.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_five_blocks = []\n    five_blocks = []\n    for block in non_zero_blocks:\n        if not np.any(block != 5):\n            five_blocks.append(block)\n        else:\n            non_five_blocks.append(block)\n    non_five_blocks.sort(key=lambda x: np.mean(np.where(x != 5)), reverse=True)\n    middle_index = len(non_five_blocks) // 2\n    sorted_blocks = non_five_blocks[:middle_index] + five_blocks + non_five_blocks[middle_index:]\n    return sorted_blocks\ndef recombine_blocks(sorted_blocks: List[np.ndarray]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of sorted non-zero blocks, this function recombines the blocks to form a 9x9 grid.\n\n    Args:\n    sorted_blocks: A list of sorted numpy arrays representing the non-zero blocks.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the 9x9 grid formed by the sorted non-zero blocks.\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = np.zeros((9, 9))\n    index = 0\n    for i in range(0, 9, 3):\n        for j in range(0, 9, 3):\n            output_grid[i:i + 3, j:j + 3] = sorted_blocks[index]\n            index += 1\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.zeros((9,9))\n    non_zero_blocks = `find the 9 3x3 blocks in the input_grid where there is no zero element in blocks, input_grid size is large than output_grid`(input_grid)\n    sorted_blocks = `sort the blocks according to the average index of non-five element and put the all-five block in the middle of the non_zero_blocks`(non_zero_blocks)\n    output_grid = `recombine the 9 3x3 blocks to a 9x9 blocks`(sorted_blocks)\n    return output_grid\n", "gpt_code": "def find_non_zero_blocks(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[np.ndarray]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, this function finds the 9 3x3 blocks where there is no zero element in the block.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of 9 numpy arrays, where each array represents a 3x3 block with no zero element.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_zero_blocks = []\n    for i in range(0, 9, 3):\n        for j in range(0, 9, 3):\n            block = input_grid[i:i + 3, j:j + 3]\n            if not np.any(block == 0):\n                non_zero_blocks.append(block)\n    return non_zero_blocks\ndef sort_blocks(non_zero_blocks: List[np.ndarray]) -> List[np.ndarray]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of non-zero blocks, this function sorts the blocks according to the average index of non-five element\n    and puts the all-five block in the middle of the non_zero_blocks.\n\n    Args:\n    non_zero_blocks: A list of numpy arrays representing the non-zero blocks.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of sorted numpy arrays, where each array represents a 3x3 block with no zero element.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_five_blocks = []\n    five_blocks = []\n    for block in non_zero_blocks:\n        if not np.any(block != 5):\n            five_blocks.append(block)\n        else:\n            non_five_blocks.append(block)\n    non_five_blocks.sort(key=lambda x: np.mean(np.where(x != 5)), reverse=True)\n    middle_index = len(non_five_blocks) // 2\n    sorted_blocks = non_five_blocks[:middle_index] + five_blocks + non_five_blocks[middle_index:]\n    return sorted_blocks\ndef recombine_blocks(sorted_blocks: List[np.ndarray]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of sorted non-zero blocks, this function recombines the blocks to form a 9x9 grid.\n\n    Args:\n    sorted_blocks: A list of sorted numpy arrays representing the non-zero blocks.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the 9x9 grid formed by the sorted non-zero blocks.\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = np.zeros((9, 9))\n    index = 0\n    for i in range(0, 9, 3):\n        for j in range(0, 9, 3):\n            output_grid[i:i + 3, j:j + 3] = sorted_blocks[index]\n            index += 1\n    return output_grid", "holes": {"find_non_zero_blocks": "find the 9 3x3 blocks in the input_grid where there is no zero element in blocks, input_grid size is large than output_grid", "sort_blocks": "sort the blocks according to the average index of non-five element and put the all-five block in the middle of the non_zero_blocks", "recombine_blocks": "recombine the 9 3x3 blocks to a 9x9 blocks"}}
