{"action": "edit", "code": "def find_non_zero_blocks(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[np.ndarray]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes an input grid and returns a list of 9 3x3 blocks where there is no zero element in the blocks.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks where there is no zero element in the blocks.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_zero_blocks = []\n    for i in range(0, input_grid.shape[0] - 2, 3):\n        for j in range(0, input_grid.shape[1] - 2, 3):\n            block = input_grid[i:i + 3, j:j + 3]\n            if np.count_nonzero(block) == 9:\n                non_zero_blocks.append(block)\n    return non_zero_blocks\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    non_zero_blocks = find_non_zero_blocks(input_grid)\n    sorted_blocks = sort_blocks(non_zero_blocks)\n    output_grid = recombine_blocks(sorted_blocks)\n    return output_grid\ndef sort_blocks(non_zero_blocks: List[np.ndarray]) -> List[np.ndarray]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks where there is no zero element in the blocks and sorts them according to the average index of non-five element and puts the all-five block in the middle of the non_zero_blocks.\n\n    Args:\n    non_zero_blocks: A list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks where there is no zero element in the blocks.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks sorted according to the average index of non-five element and with the all-five block in the middle of the non_zero_blocks.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_five_indices = []\n    for block in non_zero_blocks:\n        non_five_indices.append(np.argwhere(block != 5))\n    avg_indices = [np.mean(indices, axis=0) for indices in non_five_indices]\n    sorted_indices = np.argsort(avg_indices)\n    middle_index = sorted_indices[4]\n    sorted_blocks = [non_zero_blocks[middle_index]]\n    for i in range(4):\n        sorted_blocks.append(non_zero_blocks[sorted_indices[i]])\n        sorted_blocks.append(non_zero_blocks[sorted_indices[i + 5]])\n    return sorted_blocks\ndef recombine_blocks(blocks: List[np.ndarray]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks and recombines them to form a 9x9 numpy array.\n\n    Args:\n    blocks: A list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the recombined 9x9 grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = np.zeros((9, 9))\n    for i in range(3):\n        for j in range(3):\n            output_grid[i * 3:i * 3 + 3, j * 3:j * 3 + 3] = blocks[i * 3 + j]\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    non_zero_blocks = `find the 9 3x3 blocks in the input_grid where there is no zero element in blocks, input_grid size is large than output_grid`(input_grid)\n    sorted_blocks = `sort the blocks according to the average index of non-five element and put the all-five block in the middle of the non_zero_blocks`(non_zero_blocks)\n    output_grid = `recombine the 9 3x3 blocks to a 9x9 blocks`(sorted_blocks)\n    return output_grid\n", "gpt_code": "def find_non_zero_blocks(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> List[np.ndarray]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes an input grid and returns a list of 9 3x3 blocks where there is no zero element in the blocks.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks where there is no zero element in the blocks.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_zero_blocks = []\n    for i in range(0, input_grid.shape[0] - 2, 3):\n        for j in range(0, input_grid.shape[1] - 2, 3):\n            block = input_grid[i:i + 3, j:j + 3]\n            if np.count_nonzero(block) == 9:\n                non_zero_blocks.append(block)\n    return non_zero_blocks\ndef sort_blocks(non_zero_blocks: List[np.ndarray]) -> List[np.ndarray]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks where there is no zero element in the blocks and sorts them according to the average index of non-five element and puts the all-five block in the middle of the non_zero_blocks.\n\n    Args:\n    non_zero_blocks: A list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks where there is no zero element in the blocks.\n\n    Returns:\n    A list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks sorted according to the average index of non-five element and with the all-five block in the middle of the non_zero_blocks.\n    \"\"\"\n    non_five_indices = []\n    for block in non_zero_blocks:\n        non_five_indices.append(np.argwhere(block != 5))\n    avg_indices = [np.mean(indices, axis=0) for indices in non_five_indices]\n    sorted_indices = np.argsort(avg_indices)\n    middle_index = sorted_indices[4]\n    sorted_blocks = [non_zero_blocks[middle_index]]\n    for i in range(4):\n        sorted_blocks.append(non_zero_blocks[sorted_indices[i]])\n        sorted_blocks.append(non_zero_blocks[sorted_indices[i + 5]])\n    return sorted_blocks\ndef recombine_blocks(blocks: List[np.ndarray]) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks and recombines them to form a 9x9 numpy array.\n\n    Args:\n    blocks: A list of 9 numpy arrays representing the 3x3 blocks.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the recombined 9x9 grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = np.zeros((9, 9))\n    for i in range(3):\n        for j in range(3):\n            output_grid[i * 3:i * 3 + 3, j * 3:j * 3 + 3] = blocks[i * 3 + j]\n    return output_grid", "holes": {"find_non_zero_blocks": "find the 9 3x3 blocks in the input_grid where there is no zero element in blocks, input_grid size is large than output_grid", "sort_blocks": "sort the blocks according to the average index of non-five element and put the all-five block in the 